  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "with only one user interaction(download a malicious config), attackers can gain full command execution on the victim system.\n\nReason for inclusion in AVID: This CVE describes a command injection vulnerability in MLflow allowing remote code execution with minimal user interaction. MLflow is a software component used to build, train, package, deploy, and serve AI/ML pipelines. Exploitation would affect the AI software stack, i.e., the general-purpose AI system supply chain. It is a software vulnerability (RCE) in a core AI workflow component (mlflow), not hardware/firmware. The report provides explicit evidence (CVE ID, description, affected artifacts, references)."
  },
